OL,3,CProsecutors working 'tirelessly' to
OL,4,Cbring more convictions over violent
OL,5,Cdisorder
OL,7,FThe area's Chief Crown Prosecutor,
OL,8,FSarah Hammond, said: "We have already
OL,9,Fseen many convictions and lengthy
OL,10,Fterms of imprisonments in Mersey-
OL,11,FCheshire, and I expect this number to
OL,12,Fgrow as our prosecutors continue to
OL,13,Fwork round-the-clock."
OL,15,FThe CPS highlighted some of those
OL,16,Fjailed for their involvement in the
OL,17,Funrest in Southport.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
