OL,3,CProsecutors working 'tirelessly' to
OL,4,Cbring more convictions over violent
OL,5,Cdisorder
OL,7,F"Violence, rioting and aggression will
OL,8,Fnever be tolerated in this country,
OL,9,Fand we will continue to use the full
OL,10,Fforce of the law when charging
OL,11,Findividuals.
OL,13,F"Make no mistake, if you have taken
OL,14,Fpart in unrest either by fanning the
OL,15,Fflames online or by bringing violence
OL,16,Fand disruption to our community, you
OL,17,Fwill be caught, convicted and most
OL,18,Flikely imprisoned. It does not matter
OL,19,Fwhat your motivation may have been,
OL,20,Fyou will be prosecuted."
